This paper focuses on detecting malicious users on social media platforms, which falls under the intersection of social media analysis and cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also utilizes natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the spread of misinformation, which is a common problem in cybersecurity, making cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) another likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the malicious properties of URLs, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
